  "prompt": "Re the Sochi Olympics online video coverage, if I want to watch an event on streaming video but I cannot watch it live, is there some kind of archive after the event first airs?",
  "response": "Yes, for the Sochi Olympics, NBCOlympics.com provided a comprehensive online coverage, which included streaming video of various events. If you were unable to watch an event live, there was an archive available where you could watch the events on-demand after they had aired.\n\nHere are the key points about the Sochi Olympics online video coverage:\n\n1. **Live Streaming**: Events were streamed live on NBCOlympics.com.\n2. **On-Demand Archive**: After the live airing, most events were available in an on-demand archive, allowing viewers to watch at their convenience.\n3. **Access**: You typically needed a cable or satellite TV subscription to access the full range of content, although some free content was available.\n\nTo watch the events after they aired, you would navigate to the specific event on the NBC Olympics website, and if it had already concluded, you could find it in the \"Full Replays\" or a similar section.\n\nRemember, the availability and specifics of accessing archived content can vary, so it's always a good idea to check the official website for the most current information.",
